festival.introText:
The Big Family Day returns to Williamson Park on Sunday 14th May and it’s your chance to experience the Highest Point Festival site with all the family and lot’s to do for all.

 

For just £12 adults and £6 for the kids (5 and under go free) you can roam the entire site and take in all the sights and sounds that Highest Point offers, with a different kind of superstar lineup for all to enjoy.

 

For starters Lancaster’s very own legendary butterfly house and mini zoo is open and included in the price. So if you’ve ever wondered what meerkats get up to when they aren’t searching for car insurance or how long a caterpllar takes to become a butterfly then this wonderful year round attraction is here for you to enjoy in the ticket price.

 

Just across the courtyard inside the glorious Ashton Memorial the team from Hartbeeps are the original music story tellers and creators of multi-sensory play for babies and young children and will be running sessions all day for the young ones to enjoy. Half way up the memorial you can step outside to take in the views of the festival and across morecambe bay (we don’t call it Highest Point for nothing) whilst a few more stairs you can join the team at Magical Story Jars for adventure themed crafty story creation.

 

Every festival needs its music and family day is no different. Whether it’s dancing down in the woods to disco classics, making instruments as part of our recycled rubbish instrument workshops or learning to drum with the samba specialists Batala there’s plenty to enjoy everywhere.

 

Of course, if you want to just sit back and enjoy the main stage we’ve got some fantastic things to see and do. 

 

Whether it’s amongst the food court, inside the big top, down by the waterfall or rolling down a hill, throughout the site you will experience magnificent story telling, theatre (including a new partnership with The Dukes in Lancaster) arts, crafts and much more for everyone to enjoy with everything (apart from your food, drink and ice creams) included in your ticket price!

 

The site opens at 10am with activities ending around 4pm and the site finally closing around 6pm once you’ve had your tea. We look forward to smiling & dancing with you :)

 

Tickets on sale now!

reviews.title: Review of The Big Family Day Out
reviews.body: Edu expensive drink and food prices

reviews.title: Review of The Big Family Day Out
reviews.body: Great 2 days. Will definitely be going again next year.

reviews.title: Review of The Big Family Day Out
reviews.body: Venue is stunning  for a local festival, however for the 2nd consecutive year the queues for food/drinks were horrendous with no organisation or consideration whatsoever. Unfortunately until this has been addressed we wont be going again which is a real shame as it is great for Lancaster.

reviews.title: Review of The Big Family Day Out
reviews.body: Not enough food stalls especially for kids, the only one selling hotdogs/nuggets ran out by 1pm and theyd ran out of **tchup for the chips they did still have. None of the others sold child friendly things. The circus was continually delayed so missed it and then they finished early. Craft station ran out of stuff and poorly organised. Over an hours queue for face painting, need at least 2 more painters and no music tent this year for the kids. Beautiful surroundings let down by poor organisation and lacking activities. 2 for a can of sprite is extortionate, the rest of the food was ridiculous too. An hours wait for pizza.

reviews.title: Review of The Big Family Day Out
Review of The Big Family Day Out
reviews.body: Family-friendly festival with 2 for bottle of water

reviews.title: Review of The Big Family Day Out
Review of The Big Family Day Out
reviews.body:
Tip: Dont go to a family festival the day after the night event. The whole place stank of overflowing bins! It was horrendous.
More live music was also needed.

reviews.title: Review of The Big Family Day Out
reviews.body: Absolute lack of music.. No bands or music on the main stage (apart from children singing songs from Oliver  twice & the lottery winners).. No music on in the other tents, my son who is 4 was very disappointed & asked me wheres the music, you said it was a music festival

reviews.title: Review of The Big Family Day Out
reviews.body:
Fantastic venue for a music festival.
Would have liked to hear more local/small bands on the Sunday to give the feel of a music festival.
Would like to have been told in advance that it is a no cash festival.

faqs.question: When is The Big Family Day Out 2023?
faqs.answer: The Big Family Day Out takes place on Sunday 14th of May 2023.

faqs.question: Where is The Big Family Day Out?
faqs.answer:
The Big Family Day Out is located at Williamson Park, Lancaster.

Quernmore Rd, Lancaster LA1 1UX

faqs.question: Does The Big Family Day Out have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer: No, The Big Family Day Out is an all-ages welcome event. Children's tickets are just £6 + booking fees and Under 5s go free (ticket required)

reviewsDisplayFour.title: Review of The Big Family Day Out
reviewsDisplayFour.body: There could have been more dance areas for the children. The venue is amazing but the smell around the main stage was absolutely awful. Price for tickets was good but food/ drinks expensive.

reviewsDisplayFour.title: Review of The Big Family Day Out
reviewsDisplayFour.body: Absolutely fantastic day from start to finish! Was so much variety of things to do for all ages! Atmosphere was excellent and the entertainment was even better! Will never miss another big family day out ever again!!

reviewsDisplayFour.body: A fab family day out. The kids loved it.

reviewsDisplayFour.title: Review of The Big Family Day Out
reviewsDisplayFour.body: We had a great time lots to do and see. First time for us but definitely not the last. Well done to all involved

reviewsDisplayFour.title: Review of The Big Family Day Out
reviewsDisplayFour.body: The only downside, as with all festivals, is the toilet facilities - which degrade over the day, and by the end are not really usable.  Other festivals offer LaDeDa toilets, I would happily pay extra for these.
